Windows Labs – Answers  

10.3.1.1 Lab - Windows Installation 

The Windows operating system was installed successfully. This lab contained no questions. 

10.3.1.4 Lab - Finalize the Windows Installation 

The Windows installation was finalized successfully. This lab contained no questions. 

3.1.2.5 Lab - Search for BIOS or UEFI Firmware Updates 

The computer manufacturer’s website was visited to check for available BIOS/UEFI updates. Update instructions and version information were reviewed. 

3.1.2.7 Lab - Install Third-Party Software in Windows 

Third-party software was downloaded from a trusted source and installed successfully. The application was launched after installation to verify it works. 

10.2.1.8 Lab - Create a Partition in Windows 

Disk Management was used to create a new partition. The partition was formatted and assigned a drive letter. 

11.1.2.5 Lab - Explore the Windows Desktop 

The Windows desktop was explored, including the Start menu, taskbar, system tray, and desktop icons. 

11.1.3.4 Lab - Work with Task Manager 

Task Manager was used to view running processes, system performance, startup programs, and resource usage. 

11.1.4.11 Lab - Working with File Explorer 

File Explorer was used to browse folders, change views, manage files, and navigate the file system. 

11.2.1.5 Lab - Explore Control Panel Categories 

All Control Panel categories were explored, and common system settings were reviewed. 

11.2.2.3 Lab - User Accounts 

User accounts were viewed and managed. Account types and permissions were examined. 

11.2.5.8 Lab - Manage Virtual Memory 

Virtual memory settings were reviewed, and the paging file size was adjusted. 

11.2.6.2 Lab - Use Device Manager 

Device Manager was used to view installed hardware devices and check driver status. 

11.3.1.11 Lab - Monitor and Manage System Resources 

Part 2 (Print Spooler) was completed. The Print Spooler service was stopped and restarted. 

11.3.2.7 Lab - System Utilities 

System utilities such as Disk Cleanup and System Information were explored. 

11.3.2.8 Lab - Manage System Files 

System files were checked using system tools. The SFC command was used to scan system file integrity. 

11.4.1.5 Lab - Work in the Windows Command Shell 

The Windows Command Prompt was used to execute basic commands. 

11.4.2.7 Lab - File System Commands 

File system commands such as dir, cd, copy, and del were executed. 

11.4.3.2 Lab - Disk CLI Commands 

Disk-related command-line tools such as diskpart were used to view disks and partitions. 

11.4.4.2 Lab - Task and System CLI Commands 

Command-line tools were used to view running tasks and system information. 

11.4.5.3 Lab - Other Useful Commands 

Step 2 in Part 2 was skipped as instructed. Other useful command-line tools were explored. 

11.5.2.4 Lab - Share Resources 

This lab was completed in cooperation with another group. A folder or resource was shared and access was tested. 

11.5.6.2 Lab - Windows Remote Desktop and Assistance 

Remote Desktop was enabled and tested successfully. Part 2 (Remote Assistance) was skipped as instructed. 
